         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">25, WILTON PLACE. S.W. ¶ London ¶ Sept 20 1876 ¶ My dear Sir ¶  ¶ The Composite which has invaded Australia and of which you sent a specimen in your last letter is Inula graveolens a common weed in a ...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">76.09.20</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">From George Bentham</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">RB MSS M3, Library, Royal Botanic Gardens Melbourne.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>MS annotation by M: 'Zannich macrostem [i.e. <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Zannichellia</seg>
                     <seg style="font-style: italic; "> </seg>
                     <seg style="font-style: italic; ">macrostemon</seg>
                     <seg style="">] </seg>Anth 4-celled'. <seg style="">See M to G. Bentham, 28 November 1876.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note>
               <seg rend="form%20text" style="color: #2f5496; font-family: Times, Times; ">25, WILTON PLACE. S.W.</seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">London</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">Sept 20 1876</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">My dear Sir</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The Composite which has invaded Australia and of which you sent a specimen in your last letter is <name key="Inula%20graveolens">Inula graveolens</name> a common weed in a great part of southern Europe especially in maritime districts</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I returned to town on Wednesday last after a six weeks absence<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Bentham left London on 3 August and returned on 13 September; see B. Jackson (1906), pp. 237-8.</p>
               </note> and have now set to work at <name key="Cyperaceae">Cyperaceae</name> — I shall be anxious for the arrival of the Agamemnon with your specimens. They have sent me from Berlin on loan the Australian species published as new by Boeckeler — he has been working up the Berlin <name key="Cyperaceae">Cyperaceae</name> with great care but from what I see I scarcely think he is a good appreciator of generic and specific characters. His genus <name key="Anosporam">Anosporam</name> for instance (that is Anosporum Nees as extended by him) is a most unnatural combination of very different species of <name key="Cyperus">Cyperus</name> and <name key="Scirpus">Scirpus</name> on an imaginary character</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I hope that by this time your <name key="Gramineae">Gramineae</name> may also be on their way here.<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>See M to G. Bentham, 26 September 1876.</p>
               </note> I have been visiting at General Munro's<note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Bentham stayed with Munro from 3 to 14 August; see B. Jackson (1906), p. 237.</p>
               </note> and whilst there I took notes on all the Australian <name key="Gramineae">Gramineae</name> in his collection and with his and your assistance I hope to get through the Order rapidly Genl Munro is now preparing for De Candolle a general monograph of the whole Order and it would be rendering a service to science if you would allow me to select for him where it can be well spared a set of your Australian ones.<note xml:id="ftn5" type="footnote" n="5">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>See M to G. Bentham, 28 November 1876. Munro's monograph was not completed (<seg style="font-style: italic; ">Journal of botany, British and foreign</seg>, 1880, vol. 18, p. 96).</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I hear nothing from Wendland about your Palms — I have worked them up as well as I could with the materials I had and I returned you yours with the other specimens I still had in the box that left Kew whilst I was away but there are still two or three of Drude's species that I have not seen</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Young Balfour is working up <name key="Pandaneae">Pandaneae</name> with great care and doing them well<note xml:id="ftn6" type="footnote" n="6">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I. Balfour (1880) (read 6 December 1877, issued 31 July 1878).</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I think of beginning to print as soon as I have got through <name key="Cyperaceae">Cyperaceae</name> which if your specimens come soon will I hope be soon after Xmas</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">Ever my Dear Sir</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Yours sincerely</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>George Bentham</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Baron v. Müller</p>
